[Student "W"]
{[showcards W:SK E:S7 S:S5 N:S3]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \SK, West played the \S7 and North the \S5.

What do you play to the second trick?

Play the \D10, NOT another \S.

You can see the \S6, \S5, \S4, \S3 and \S2. So the \S7 is West's lowest \S, he is doing his best to discourage you from leading the suit again.

North held up with \S A J x, hoping you would play the suit again and give him two tricks.

If you play the \D10 West will win the \DA and return a \S, allowing you to drive out North's \SA while you still have the \CA for an entry.}
[Play "W"]SK

